<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="LimitCont" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>g(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        g(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b + x, &amp; x &lt; 2 \\\
                        x^{2} - 6 \, x + 10, &amp; x \geq 2
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>The function <m>h(x)</m> is discontinuous at <m>x=4</m>. Determine if <m>h(x)</m> is left- or right-continuous and classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=4</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        h(x) = \begin{cases}
                        -\frac{1}{2} \, x + 8, &amp; x \leq 4 \\\
                        \frac{x^{2} - 9 \, x + 14}{x + 4}, &amp; x &gt; 4
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>g(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>, let <m>b=0</m>.</li>
            <li>The function <m>h(x)</m> has a jump discontinuity and is left-continuous at <m>x=4</m>.</li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
